gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 122, Pelicans 101
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Pelicans, 122-101. Anthony Edwards led the way for the Timberwolves with 26 points and eight assists, while Karl-Anthony Towns (23 points) and Rudy Gobert (17 points, 20 rebounds) added a combined 40 points in the victory. Brandon Ingram tallied a team-high 24 points, along with six assists for the Pelicans in the losing effort. The Timberwolves improve to 5-2 on the season, while the Pelicans fall to 4-4.
